<HEADLINE>
U.S. CYCLIST TAKES LEAD IN 2007 TOUR DE TAIWAN IN KAOHSIUNG
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March 18 (CNA) 03/18/07  23:15:16 (By Y.L. Kao)
</P>
<P>
U.S. cyclist Shawn Milne of the Maxxis team won the first stage
of the 2007 Tour de Taiwan international cycling event Sunday,
with Askari Hossein of the Giant Asian Racing Team snatching
first place in Asian racing category, and Wu Po-hung coming in as
the top-ranked Taiwanese rider.
</P>
<P>
The first stage of the race opened Sunday along the banks of the
Love River in Kaohsiung City after Legislator Huang Chao-shun,
who is also president of the event-organizing  Chinese Taipei
Cycling Association, and Kaohsiung Mayor Chen Chu led racers
cycling around the Love River.
</P>
<P>
A total of 19 teams consisting of 100-plus racers from 15
countries dashed out from the Kaohsiung History Museum following
the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
In the beginning, Australia's Lapthorne Darren and his Drapac
Porsche took the lead, while Hossein,  Griffin Paul and Peng
Kuei-hsiang geared up and joined the lead riders.
</P>
<P>
The situation changed after Shawn,  and Luxembourg's  Poos
Christian of the Differdange team, Darren and Hossein formed the
leading squad.
</P>
<P>
Riding in second place for much of the race, Shawn was able to
speed ahead and take the stage with a time of one hour 57 minutes
and 21 seconds.
</P>
<P>
This was the fourth time in its 20-year history that the race has
opened in Kaohsiung City. Mayor Chen welcomed the contestants and
voiced hope that all of them would enjoy the beauty of Kaohsiung
and the hospitality and kindness of local residents.
</P>
<P>
Chen also said that the municipal government will spare no effort
in its bid to host other sports activities in addition to the
2009 World Games, which is slated to be held in the southern port
city.
</P>
<P>
The cycling route, which stretches a total of 88 kilometers, was
designed to surround the inner-city main streets.
</P>
<P>
The Tour de Taiwan will cover seven stages around the island. In
addition to the first leg in Kaohsiung, the others will be as
following: 3/19 stage 2 Pingtung Circuit, 113.6 kilometers, 3/20
stage 3 Chiayi Circuit 131.5 kilometer, 3/21 stage 4 Changhua
117.4 km, 3/22 stage 5 Taichung City, 3/23 stage 6 Changhua-
Taipei Bali 118.9 km and 3/24 stage 7 Taipei Municipal Government
60 km.
</P>
